                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="76.0" layoutY="365.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="This is because C is considered the &quot;mother of programming languages&quot; and is one of the most foundational languages of computer science." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="76.0" layoutY="672.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="One of the strengths of C is its simplicity. It has a small set of keywords and a clean, readable syntax that makes it easy for beginners to learn. Despite its simplicity, C is very powerful and flexible. It supports structured programming, allowing developers to write clean, logical, and reusable code using functions, loops, and conditionals." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="76.0" layoutY="780.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Learning C is a great starting point for any aspiring programmer. It helps build a strong foundation in programming logic, problem-solving, and understanding how programs run at a lower level. By learning C, you'll not only be able to write efficient programs but also gain skills that are transferable to many other programming languages and technologies." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
