                  <Text layoutX="76.0" layoutY="1223.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Now that you’ve been introduced to the basics of C programming, you’ve taken the first step toward understanding how software interacts closely with hardware. C provides a strong foundation that will help you learn more advanced languages and concepts in the future. With its simple yet powerful structure, C encourages you to think logically and write efficient code. As you move forward, continue practicing by writing small programs and exploring how each part of the language works. This is just the beginning of your programming journey—keep building, keep experimenting, and keep learning!" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
